The Euclidean algorithm works by repeatedly applying the division algorithm to find the remainder of the division of one number by another. The remainder is the divisor, and the divisor is the remainder of the previous division. This process is repeated until the remainder is zero, at which point the divisor is the GCD of the original two numbers.

def gcf(a, b):
